# Copy this file to .env.local and fill in what you have.
# Nothing here is required to run the app — everything can also be set
# from the Settings page in the UI, which is usually easier since it
# saves straight to data/db.json. This file is only useful if you'd
# rather manage secrets as environment variables (e.g. for deploying
# somewhere later).

# Not currently read directly by the app (settings are stored via the UI),
# kept here as a reference for what you'll need to gather:

# GHL_PRIVATE_TOKEN=pit-xxxxxxxx
# GHL_LOCATION_ID=xxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxx
# ANTHROPIC_API_KEY=sk-ant-xxxxxxxx
# SKOOL_WEBHOOK_SECRET=choose-any-random-string
